Turkey Stocks: Besiktas, Kerevitas Gida, Koza Altin Are Active

-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 
2011-08-22T14:52:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-18/anadolu-efes-coca-cola-icecek-erdemir-turkey-stocks-preview.html
Turkey ’s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index (XU100)  gained for a second day, adding 225.29, or 0.4 percent, to
53,287.03 at the 5:30 p.m. close in Istanbul.  The following stocks were active. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Besiktas Futbol Yatirimlari Sanayi & Ticaret AS (BJKAS TI),
the merchandising arm of the Istanbul-based  soccer club , fell 26
kurus, or 3.1 percent, to 8.08 liras. The team’s chairman will
be called in for questioning in an ongoing probe into league-
wide match-fixing in Turkey, CNBC-e television reported, while
 UEFA ’s chief investigator will visit the country to gather
information and prepare a report, according to Milliyet
newspaper.  Kerevitas Gida Sanayi & Ticaret AS (KERVT TI), a maker of
canned and frozen food, fell as much as 5.8 percent before
closing down 50 kurus, or 1 percent, at 51.5 liras. The second-
quarter loss widened to 4.54 million liras ($2.5 million) from
1.83 million liras a year earlier, the company said.  Koza Altin Isletmeleri AS (KOZAL)  , a gold miner, gained
80 kurus, or 3.3 percent, to 25 liras, its highest since Aug. 4.
Gold reached a record high of $1,894.8 per ounce.  To contact the reporter on this story:
